$ Office Ribbon: File -> Options -> General
@ General

*File -> Options -> General* allows to set, well, *general options* for working with → Microsoft/Office/Word[Word], → Microsoft/Office/Excel[Excel] etc.

{ User interface options

  Options:
    • Show Mini Toolbar on selection
    • Enable Live Preview
    • Screen Tip style (Show/don't show feature descriptions in ScreenTips; don't show ScreenTips)

  Excel also has: Show Quick Analysis options on selection.

  Word also has: Update document content while dragging.

}

{ Personalize your copy of Microsoft Office #office-file-options-general-personalize

  Options include
    • User name
    • Initials
    • Always use these values regardless of sign in to Office
    • Office Theme (Colorful, Dark Gray, White)

  TODO: Are *user name* and *initials* stored in the registry under
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/Common/UserInfo[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\Common\UserInfo`]?

}

{ Start up options

  Options to choose from:
    • Choose the extensions you want … to open by default
    • Tell me if Microsoft … is't the default program for viewing and editing …
    • Show the Start screen when this application starts (Compare with the → Microsoft/Office/Excel#excel-command-line-parameters[Excel command line parameter `/e`])
}

sa:

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/General[File -> Options -> General] for Excel.
